<doc id="77114" wikidata="Q236284" url="?curid=77114" title="473 BC">
<text>Year 473 BC was a year of the pre-Julian Roman calendar. At the time, it was known as the Year of the Consulship of Mamercus and Iullus (or, less frequently, year 281 &quot;[[Ab urbe condita]]&quot;). The denomination 473 BC for this year has been used since the early medieval period, when the Anno Domini calendar era became the prevalent method in Europe for naming years.

